51.1	Flying_Tigers	Flying Tigers	The 1st American Volunteer Group (AVG) of the Chinese Air Force in 1941â€“1942, famously nicknamed the Flying Tigers, was composed of pilots from the United States Army (USAAF), Navy (USN), and Marine Corps (USMC), recruited under presidential sanction and commanded by Claire Lee Chennault. The ground crew and headquarters staff were likewise mostly recruited from the U.S. military, along with some civilians.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Flying_Tigers_personnel.jpg/300px-Flying_Tigers_personnel.jpg
